### ========================================
### Demo.Api - Consolidated Test Requests
### Demonstrates all Acontplus libraries and features
### ========================================
### Environment variables defined in http-client.env.json (Rider/IntelliJ)
### For Visual Studio, change @baseUrl manually or use settings.json

# @baseUrl = {{baseUrl}}
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7111

### ========================================
### 1. BARCODE & REPORTS
### ========================================

### Generate QR Code/Barcode
GET {{baseUrl}}/barcode?text=HelloWorld&includeLabel=true

### Generate Sample Invoice Report
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/sample-invoice

### ========================================
### 2. XADES-BES SIGNING (Acontplus.Billing)
### ========================================
### Signs an unsigned SRI comprobante XML with XAdES-BES (RSA-SHA1).
### Returns the signed XML as a downloadable file ready for SRI reception.
###
### Replace the file paths with real local files before running:
###   - xmlFile  : unsigned comprobante (e.g. factura_unsigned.xml)
###   - pfxFile  : your PFX/P12 certificate (e.g. certificate.p12)
###   - pfxPassword : password protecting the certificate
###   - claveAcceso : 49-digit SRI access key

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/billing/sign
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----SriBoundary

------SriBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="xmlFile"; filename="factura_unsigned.xml"
Content-Type: text/xml

< ./factura_unsigned.xml
------SriBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pfxFile"; filename="certificate.p12"
Content-Type: application/x-pkcs12

< ./certificate.p12
------SriBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="pfxPassword"

YourCertificatePassword
------SriBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="claveAcceso"

2905202601179265679300110010010000000011234567890
------SriBoundary--



### Generate Sample Customers Report
GET {{baseUrl}}/reports/sample-customers?format=PDF

### ========================================
### 2. USUARIO (USER) CRUD OPERATIONS
### ========================================

### Get all users (paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10

### Get users - with search and sorting
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10&searchTerm=ivan&sortBy=Email&sortDirection=Asc

### Get users - with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10&filters[status]=Active&filters[role]=Admin

### Get user by ID
@userId=1
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/{{userId}}

### Create new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "ivan",
  "email": "ivan@gmail.com"
}

### Update user
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "emilio.senguana",
  "email": "sengua2000@gmail.dev"
}

### Delete user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/{{userId}}

### ========================================
### 3. ADO REPOSITORY - ADVANCED QUERIES
### ========================================

### Get users (legacy ADO stored procedure)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/legacy-ado

### Get dynamic users (schema-less response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/get-dynamic

### Get user count (scalar query)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/count

### Check if username exists
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/exists/admin

### Get active users count (modified in last 6 months)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/active-count

### Get paginated users (ADO) - basic
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-ado?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10

### Get paginated users (ADO) - with search and sorting
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-ado?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10&searchTerm=ivan&sortBy=CreatedAt&sortDirection=Desc

### Get paginated users (ADO) - with filters[showDeleted, minAge, role]
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-ado?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10&filters[showDeleted]=false&filters[minAge]=18&filters[role]=Admin&filters[createdAfter]=2026-05-17

### Get paginated users (ADO) - with createdAfter date filter
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-ado?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10&filters[createdAfter]=2026-01-01&filters[showDeleted]=false

### Get paginated users (ADO) - full example
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-ado?pageIndex=1&pageSize=10&searchTerm=ivan&sortBy=CreatedAt&sortDirection=Desc&filters[showDeleted]=false&filters[minAge]=18&filters[role]=Admin&filters[createdAfter]=2026-01-01

### Get paginated users with complex server-side filters (last 30 days, IsDeleted=false)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-complex?pageIndex=1&pageSize=20&sortBy=Email&sortDirection=Asc

### Get paginated users with complex filters - with search
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-complex?pageIndex=1&pageSize=20&searchTerm=ivan&sortBy=CreatedAt&sortDirection=Desc

### Get paginated users from stored procedure
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-sp?pageIndex=1&pageSize=15&sortBy=Username&sortDirection=Asc

### Get paginated users from stored procedure - with search
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/paged-sp?pageIndex=1&pageSize=15&searchTerm=admin&sortBy=Username&sortDirection=Asc

### Bulk insert users
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/bulk
Content-Type: application/json

[
  { "username": "bulk_user_1", "email": "bulk1@example.com" },
  { "username": "bulk_user_2", "email": "bulk2@example.com" },
  { "username": "bulk_user_3", "email": "bulk3@example.com" }
]

### Execute batch operations
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/batch
Content-Type: application/json

[1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

### Test exception handling
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/test-exception/1

### Test custom error
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/usuario/test-custom-error/3

